BB Code (bulletin board code) is a collection of formatting tags. Tags are placed in Square Brackets [command]  and an [/command] at the end of the affected text (with the exception of [ line] which does nit need to be closed). While there are many flavors of BB Code in existence, this guide includes the ones applicable to  creating and updating [library] pages for FarmRPG. In this guide, there's an extra space in the example brackets to show unparsed code. 
[color=cornflowerblue][b][i]I highly recommend using a backup page to make edits for anything that you'll be sad about if it accidentally gets deleted/messed up. Accidents do happen, especially when editing on mobile.[s]NVS accidentally deleted the entire faq once. Rkm13 deleted the staff page.[/s][/i][/b][/color]Spacings can look wonky sometimes, so use your backup pages to test how things look![line][color=#2B5BCC]Blue Color[/color] - [color =#2B5BCC]Blue Color[/color]
