Tables: Tables use A TR (Table Row), TH (Table Header), and TD (Table Data) headers. TR needs to be at the start and end of every row. TH will make a cell have bold text

[table][tr][th]Runestone[/th][th]Location[/th][/tr][tr][td]  #1[/td][td]Carrot[/td][/tr][tr][td]  #2[/td][td]Farm Pond[/td][/tr][tr][td]  #3[/td][td]Forest Pond[/td][/tr][tr][td]  #4[/td][td]Small Cave[/td][/tr][tr][td] #5[/td][td]Misty Forest[/td][/tr][tr][td] #6[/td][td]Cucumber[/td][/tr][tr][td] #7[/td][td]Radish[/td][/tr][tr][td]  #8[/td][td]Small Pond[/td][/tr][tr][td]  #9[/td][td]Black Rock Canyon[/td][/tr][tr][td]  #10[/td][td]Leek[/td][/tr][/table]

[ table][ tr][ th]Runestone[ /th][ th]Location[ /th][ /tr][ tr][ td]  #1[ /td][ td]Carrot[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td]  #2[ /td][ td]Farm Pond[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td]  #3[ /td][ td]Forest Pond[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td]  #4[ /td][ td]Small Cave[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td] #5[ /td][ td]Misty Forest[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td] #6[ /td][ td]Cucumber[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td] #7[ /td][ td]Radish[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td]  #8[ /td][ td]Small Pond[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td]  #9[ /td][ td]Black Rock Canyon[ /td][ /tr][ tr][ td]  #10[ /td][ td]Leek[ /td][ /tr][ /table]

While formatting tables in a word editor (I build them in Excel, them copy them into Notepad++ to use search and replace to add all the tags) it is easier to keep each row on its own line. However, when pasted into the wiki, you want to remove all the carriage returns, and have the full code be on one line, or else it will put a bunch of extra white space above the table.